ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The DEFRA assessment provides a useful summary
of the current FMD situation in Thrace. Readers
are referred to the Turkish report of 28 Feb 2007
(ref 20070301.0726), wherein the source of
infection was claimed to be contact with wild
species, further identified as an infected boar.
It will be interesting to obtain additional
information on this potential source of infection
for livestock, in Turkey as well as in other
Middle-Eastern countries. Swine are known to be
effective propagators of the FMD virus and
significant source for its airborne spread. Wild
boar populations of considerable sizes and
density are believed to be present in several
regional countries. Their possible role as
potential disseminators of the FMD virus in the
region deserves adequate study. - Mod.AS].
